why is my month old bad i have an month old son and every time we go to the store he acts really bad he will cry and cry he does this everytime at any store it is really hard to go shopping sometimes we just give up and leave how do you discipline a month old is there any way i have a year old also and he never acted like this so i don't know what to do kids are so different aren't they some things to try make sure he's fed and rested before you go bring a snack or a favorite toy carry him on your hip let him walk or put him in a backpack instead of a cart keep a running dialog or sing to distract him try taking him shopping a couple times when you don't need anything at all just walk around together and look at things and have fun so he gets used to shopping being mommy time find a grocery store with one of those cool shopping carts that look like cars whenever possible shop without the kids don't give up crying is not being bad when you're not old enough to have other ways to express yourself when he is talking more you'll be fine in the meantime sometimes you really just have to leave the store good luck Target Corporation The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Supermarket About a Boy Social rule Trailer Park Boys Shaggy dog story Jackass: The Movie Cardcaptor Sakura Teen Girl Squad Theory of conduct Shopping cart RuneScape locations Time Out of Mind The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Journey (band) The Shining (film) Kimi Finster Street-Legal The Adventures of Pete & Pete The McGuire Sisters Aerial (dance move) The Regina Monologues Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) AFI 100 Years series Invader Zim Indianapolis 500 Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Luck Pitaten Episodes of Lost (Season 1) The Inside Garfield Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina 1957 World Series The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Procrastination Nico Robin Ice cream Ocean's Twelve Reservoir Dogs Survivor (novel) El Chavo del Ocho The Apprentice 2 Similarities between the Bible and t